 Usage Instructions

1. Download or clone the project repository to your local system.
2. Open the project folder and launch the `index.html` file in a modern web browser such as Chrome, Microsoft Edge, or Firefox.
3. Allow camera or Bluetooth permissions if prompted (only if those features are implemented in the project).
4. The application will display the radiation monitoring interface.
5. In simulation mode, the system generates and displays simulated radiation values that update automatically at regular intervals.
6. If an external radiation sensor is connected via Bluetooth or USB, the application will receive and display real-time radiation measurements from the device.
7. Monitor the displayed radiation values and any warning messages or alerts if the readings exceed the predefined safety threshold.
8. To stop monitoring, close the browser tab or disconnect the external radiation sensor.
